               layout and the ubus protocol constants (MSG_*/ATTR_*) as
               declared in ubus ubusmsg.h (LGPL-2.1); these are uncopyrightable
               protocol facts (integer constants + a packed struct),
               re-derivable from the `ubus -S` golden captures the module is
               tested against. libubus-io.c (LGPL-2.1) contributed NO code: the
               unix-socket transport (blocking read/write loops, single-buffer
               send, fixed-header framing, seq-matched request/reply) is an
               independent implementation — none of libubus-io.c's expression
               (writev/iovec scatter-gather, chunked reader, SCM_RIGHTS
               fd-passing, callback request-registry, reconnect state machine)
               is present. Byte-parity verified against `ubus -S` on real
               hardware. Published under MIT; the only copyleft touchpoint is
               the uncopyrightable ubus protocol facts above.

